3
00:01:59,345 --> 00:02:00,100
But it's okay.

4
00:02:00,325 --> 00:02:02,166
Get ready for the contest this afternoon.

5
00:02:02,491 --> 00:02:03,241
Hold on.

6
00:02:03,441 --> 00:02:05,691
There's another matter.

7
00:02:05,766 --> 00:02:06,266
What?

8
00:02:13,591 --> 00:02:14,041
Here you go.

9
00:02:17,616 --> 00:02:18,366
This is the one.

10
00:02:19,066 --> 00:02:19,941
Everyone says this God of Earth

11
00:02:20,141 --> 00:02:21,221
can make your dreams come true,

12
00:02:23,516 --> 00:02:25,766
especially love matter.

13
00:02:28,691 --> 00:02:32,166
God, please help me pass the contest.

14
00:02:32,341 --> 00:02:33,666
If I pass it,

15
00:02:33,741 --> 00:02:37,441
Mek and I will run around
the school park naked to repay you.

16
00:02:37,441 --> 00:02:38,766
Sadhu.

17
00:02:39,091 --> 00:02:40,991
Hey, why am I involved?

18
00:02:42,066 --> 00:02:43,477
I don't dare to run around naked alone.

19
00:02:43,477 --> 00:02:44,117
I'm shy.

20
00:02:44,891 --> 00:02:46,291
Do you think I'm not shy?

21
00:02:47,741 --> 00:02:49,666
Okay. That can do.

22
00:02:51,466 --> 00:02:53,941
God, my friend is shy.

23
00:02:54,516 --> 00:02:56,066
I'll change the way of praying.

24
00:02:56,291 --> 00:03:00,816
My friend and I will run around
the school park in school uniform.

25
00:03:00,866 --> 00:03:02,366
Sadhu.

26
00:03:03,091 --> 00:03:04,266
Does that count?

27
00:03:04,716 --> 00:03:05,441
Of course.

28
00:03:05,466 --> 00:03:08,416
You know that nowadays

29
00:03:08,416 --> 00:03:09,656
it's harder for someone to run

30
00:03:10,116 --> 00:03:12,832
in school uniform than naked.

31
00:03:36,391 --> 00:03:36,916
Hey.

32
00:03:37,541 --> 00:03:37,916
What?

33
00:03:38,441 --> 00:03:39,441
I almost forgot.

34
00:03:41,066 --> 00:03:44,541
Everyone says this God of Earth
likes to watch believers dance.

35
00:03:45,541 --> 00:03:48,716
Those who perform for him when praying,

36
00:03:49,816 --> 00:03:52,616
their wishes will come true faster.

37
00:03:53,266 --> 00:03:54,516
So what? What do you want to do?

38
00:03:56,441 --> 00:03:59,091
I want to perform for him.

39
00:04:03,041 --> 00:04:03,541
How?

40
00:04:04,616 --> 00:04:06,366
You know how to dance?

41
00:04:06,591 --> 00:04:09,691
I have learnt a little bit
of ballroom dance before.

42
00:04:10,162 --> 00:04:11,716
I can somehow dance.

43
00:04:12,166 --> 00:04:14,316
But ballroom dance
has to be done in pair, right?

44
00:04:15,891 --> 00:04:18,391
Hence you, my hubby,

45
00:04:18,391 --> 00:04:20,016
have to dance with your wife.

46
00:04:20,016 --> 00:04:21,666
Please.

47
00:04:21,866 --> 00:04:22,466
No way.

48
00:04:25,391 --> 00:04:26,541
Help me, please.

49
00:04:26,816 --> 00:04:29,441
Your wish will come true.

50
00:04:29,866 --> 00:04:32,616
Why should I do this thing?

51
00:04:34,716 --> 00:04:37,241
Here, over here.

52
00:04:38,916 --> 00:04:39,541
Are you ready?

53
00:05:01,041 --> 00:05:13,841
♪Give someone you love your entire heart♪

54
00:05:15,766 --> 00:05:21,016
♪Don't mind what others think♪

55
00:05:21,016 --> 00:05:27,941
♪It doesn't matter if it's heaven or earth♪

56
00:05:28,866 --> 00:05:33,591
♪A feeling has no reason♪

57
00:05:33,691 --> 00:05:38,016
♪If love sprouts at the bottom of your heart♪

58
00:05:38,016 --> 00:05:42,266
♪Let it grow at its will♪

59
00:05:47,041 --> 00:05:54,266
♪I want to tell you, beautiful love has no rules♪

60
00:05:54,291 --> 00:05:55,841
♪No matter male or female♪

61
00:05:55,841 --> 00:05:57,041
The performance is done.

62
00:05:57,041 --> 00:05:58,141
♪as long as you love me♪

63
00:05:58,141 --> 00:05:59,766
Thank you.

64
00:05:59,766 --> 00:06:01,966
My love has to come true.

65
00:06:02,266 --> 00:06:03,191
♪Most importantly♪

66
00:06:03,191 --> 00:06:03,941
I'll leave now.

67
00:06:03,941 --> 00:06:09,591
♪someone knows my thought♪

68
00:06:09,591 --> 00:06:11,791
♪Leave the rules aside♪
♪Let our love grow♪

69
00:06:11,791 --> 00:06:13,591
I hope my wish will come true too.

70
00:06:13,591 --> 00:06:19,241
♪Leave the rules aside
♪Let our love grow♪

71
00:06:23,066 --> 00:06:25,166
Mother, you're awake?

72
00:06:25,991 --> 00:06:27,416
Mother, what's going on?

73
00:06:27,516 --> 00:06:28,716
Does it hurt?

74
00:06:29,116 --> 00:06:30,666
Have you eaten?

75
00:06:32,616 --> 00:06:33,491
Sit down, sweetie.

76
00:06:34,191 --> 00:06:35,741
I'll answer your questions one by one.

77
00:06:36,291 --> 00:06:38,091
I'm fine right now.

78
00:06:38,441 --> 00:06:40,091
So, don't worry.

79
00:06:40,291 --> 00:06:41,491
I'll recover soon.

80
00:06:51,741 --> 00:06:52,191
Then...

81
00:06:53,141 --> 00:06:55,216
What book are you reading?
There are so many of them.

82
00:06:55,341 --> 00:06:56,316
Oh.

83
00:06:57,041 --> 00:06:59,416
A medical student gave it to me.

84
00:06:59,816 --> 00:07:02,916
He told me a lot about medical knowledge.

85
00:07:04,966 --> 00:07:06,766
He also told me that...

86
00:07:06,891 --> 00:07:08,541
his father also had cancer.

87
00:07:08,716 --> 00:07:11,241
But it was diagnosed too late.

88
00:07:11,241 --> 00:07:12,591
The treatment wasn't in time.

89
00:07:13,391 --> 00:07:15,741
So he asked me to learn these.

90
00:07:19,991 --> 00:07:20,766
By the way,

91
00:07:20,941 --> 00:07:24,216
He even brought me flowers yesterday.

92
00:07:24,341 --> 00:07:26,816
He said I would be cheered up when I saw them,

93
00:07:26,866 --> 00:07:28,016
so I can recover faster.

94
00:07:45,191 --> 00:07:46,191
Let me help you.

95
00:07:49,716 --> 00:07:50,366
Thank you.

96
00:08:02,591 --> 00:08:03,616
Is there anything?

97
00:08:04,741 --> 00:08:05,366
Nothing.

98
00:08:07,816 --> 00:08:08,691
That day,

99
00:08:09,341 --> 00:08:10,466
when I said something bad to you,

100
00:08:12,066 --> 00:08:13,091
I'm so sorry.

101
00:08:17,341 --> 00:08:18,366
It's okay.

102
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:21,541
Everyone would be worried,
when facing such a matter.

103
00:08:23,366 --> 00:08:26,416
Such a matter makes me feel horrible,

104
00:08:26,991 --> 00:08:28,641
because I feel helpless.

105
00:08:29,491 --> 00:08:30,766
I could only wait for the examination report.

106
00:08:30,991 --> 00:08:33,966
I don't know what will happen to my mother.

107
00:08:36,191 --> 00:08:37,816
Actually, there's much you can do.

108
00:08:38,991 --> 00:08:40,766
You have a cute smile.

109
00:08:41,641 --> 00:08:44,016
If your mother can see your smile every day,

110
00:08:44,166 --> 00:08:47,066
I think she'll be more confident.

111
00:08:48,591 --> 00:08:50,741
Thank you, doctor.

112
00:08:52,066 --> 00:08:53,641
I'm only a medical student.

113
00:08:54,166 --> 00:08:55,616
Just call me Senior Thara.

114
00:08:56,441 --> 00:08:59,541
But you'll be a doctor in the future.

115
00:08:59,916 --> 00:09:02,991
Then I shall call you Brother Doctor.

116
00:09:05,166 --> 00:09:06,016
Up to you.

117
00:09:08,891 --> 00:09:09,416
Okay.

118
00:09:30,916 --> 00:09:31,691
Sore throat?

119
00:09:31,966 --> 00:09:34,191
What kind of flower you brought for me today?

120
00:09:34,441 --> 00:09:36,491
I passed by the wet market today.

121
00:09:36,741 --> 00:09:38,916
So I brought you this flower.

122
00:09:42,716 --> 00:09:43,591
Cauliflower?

123
00:09:44,516 --> 00:09:46,641
Do you want me to cook it?

124
00:09:47,891 --> 00:09:49,991
I was in a hurry.
This is the only thing I could get.

125
00:09:50,116 --> 00:09:51,066
Do you want it or not?

126
00:09:54,691 --> 00:09:55,291
Alright.

127
00:09:58,316 --> 00:10:00,916
But since you brought cauliflower,

128
00:10:02,841 --> 00:10:04,741
why don't you sleep in my apartment tonight,

129
00:10:05,641 --> 00:10:06,866
and cook this for me?

130
00:10:14,066 --> 00:10:15,316
Let go of me.

131
00:10:33,441 --> 00:10:34,066
Are you ready?

132
00:10:41,891 --> 00:10:42,741
No.

133
00:10:52,391 --> 00:10:52,991
Hold on.

134
00:10:53,391 --> 00:10:54,341
I'm not ready.

135
00:11:06,966 --> 00:11:07,941
No, Bohn.

136
00:11:08,391 --> 00:11:09,491
What are you doing to me?

137
00:11:10,191 --> 00:11:11,266
I'm not ready.

138
00:11:16,566 --> 00:11:17,691
What are you afraid of?

139
00:11:18,816 --> 00:11:20,366
I just want you to cook for me.

140
00:11:22,616 --> 00:11:23,741
Oh.

141
00:11:24,566 --> 00:11:26,416
I thought you want me
to do something else.

142
00:11:27,116 --> 00:11:28,691
Okay, I'll cook for you immediately.

143
00:11:40,916 --> 00:11:41,866
Give me an onion.

144
00:11:49,466 --> 00:11:50,491
Get lost.

145
00:11:51,416 --> 00:11:52,791
You're always using the same trick.

146
00:11:53,841 --> 00:11:54,466
Stupid.

147
00:11:58,816 --> 00:12:00,716
I'm going to cut this cauliflower now.

148
00:12:01,741 --> 00:12:03,016
Do you want to take a photo of it?

149
00:12:03,166 --> 00:12:04,041
Hurry, cut it.

150
00:12:04,966 --> 00:12:06,366
Who would want to take
a photo of such a flower?

151
00:12:25,266 --> 00:12:26,541
-Hello.
-Hello.

152
00:12:26,991 --> 00:12:28,716
-I should sign here, right?
-Yes.

153
00:12:30,391 --> 00:12:31,041
This is my registration form.

154
00:12:31,041 --> 00:12:31,766
Okay.

155
00:12:41,141 --> 00:12:42,466
Please have a sit.

156
00:12:42,491 --> 00:12:43,059
Okay, sir.

157
00:12:43,059 --> 00:12:44,416
-Thank you, sir.
-Thank you.

158
00:13:12,741 --> 00:13:13,216
Oh.

159
00:13:25,691 --> 00:13:27,291
Are you Thannanee?

160
00:13:27,841 --> 00:13:28,341
Yes.

161
00:13:28,541 --> 00:13:29,616
This way, please.

162
00:13:33,841 --> 00:13:35,541
It's going to start.

163
00:13:56,216 --> 00:13:57,091
Hello.

164
00:13:57,391 --> 00:13:57,941
Hello.

165
00:13:57,941 --> 00:13:59,691
Please let me tune my guitar first.

166
00:14:02,441 --> 00:14:03,291
Hold on a second.

167
00:14:09,941 --> 00:14:10,548
Young boy.

168
00:14:10,548 --> 00:14:11,866
This is a new song, Miss.

169
00:14:11,891 --> 00:14:13,241
It hasn't been released.

170
00:14:13,441 --> 00:14:14,866
This is its first appearance.

171
00:14:15,666 --> 00:14:17,666
I'm the manager of Fon.

172
00:14:19,891 --> 00:14:21,716
You're Fon's friend, right?

173
00:14:22,566 --> 00:14:23,016
Yes.

174
00:14:23,091 --> 00:14:24,641
You're joining today's contest,

175
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:27,266
so you can get close to Fon
if you're chosen, right?

176
00:14:28,541 --> 00:14:31,516
I admire you for contributing so much.

177
00:14:31,816 --> 00:14:36,666
But Fon is working hard to become a celebrity.

178
00:14:37,141 --> 00:14:38,891
And this is inappropriate.

179
00:14:39,541 --> 00:14:43,441
Your goodwill would destroy all her hard work.

180
00:14:44,866 --> 00:14:47,666
If you really love her, you should know

181
00:14:48,466 --> 00:14:50,366
what you should do.

182
00:15:03,891 --> 00:15:06,466
Hello, I'm Fon, TRI28.

183
00:15:07,816 --> 00:15:10,766
How did you feel when you join
the big family of TRI28?

184
00:15:10,766 --> 00:15:15,816
I was very excited and happy
at the same time.

185
00:15:15,816 --> 00:15:19,816
Because winning this contest is my dream
since I was a child.

186
00:15:19,916 --> 00:15:25,341
I want to become a celebrity
to make good productions for everyone.

187
00:15:25,341 --> 00:15:28,916
You're a beautiful girl, do have
someone who understands you?

188
00:15:29,341 --> 00:15:31,941
Someone who understands me? No.

189
00:15:31,941 --> 00:15:35,841
Because I want to give my best
to sprint on this path.

190
00:15:35,841 --> 00:15:38,866
I hope that everyone will support me.

191
00:16:53,316 --> 00:16:53,841
Hi, mom.

192
00:16:53,891 --> 00:16:55,741
Hi, you're back already.

193
00:16:56,116 --> 00:16:56,791
Where's dad?

194
00:16:56,891 --> 00:16:59,116
Your dad is out of town for a meeting.

195
00:16:59,391 --> 00:17:03,316
He should be back sometime tonight.

196
00:17:05,966 --> 00:17:10,166
And did he say where he's going
and who he's going with?

197
00:17:10,991 --> 00:17:12,766
I don't know. He didn't tell me.

198
00:17:19,841 --> 00:17:22,441
Why are you asking about him so much today?

199
00:17:23,916 --> 00:17:24,716
It's nothing.

200
00:17:26,766 --> 00:17:29,951
Rud, can you help me bring in
the clothes?

201
00:17:30,266 --> 00:17:30,966
Sure, mom.

202
00:17:50,741 --> 00:17:51,716
Are you still troubled?

203
00:17:52,516 --> 00:17:54,291
If not, click in to see the photos
I uploaded yesterday.

204
00:17:56,241 --> 00:17:58,091
Or are you even more troubled now?

205
00:18:07,166 --> 00:18:08,915
[Pin: Let's go on hand-in-hand.]

206
00:18:18,216 --> 00:18:22,491
Everyone has a good and a bad side.

207
00:18:23,291 --> 00:18:26,491
But I'm sure he has his reason
when he does such a thing.

208
00:18:57,691 --> 00:19:00,541
Do not cross this pillow tonight, understand?

209
00:19:01,741 --> 00:19:02,441
What does this mean?

210
00:19:02,791 --> 00:19:05,416
I agreed to sleep with you,
but I didn't agree on everything.

211
00:19:07,066 --> 00:19:08,316
Please understand correctly.

212
00:19:09,041 --> 00:19:10,041
Duen.

213
00:19:35,191 --> 00:19:35,916
Ram.

214
00:19:38,916 --> 00:19:39,791
Where are you going?

215
00:19:40,591 --> 00:19:41,541
What's going on?

216
00:19:49,341 --> 00:19:50,891
I know about you and Pin.

217
00:19:57,766 --> 00:19:58,866
Aren't you going to explain?

218
00:20:01,391 --> 00:20:02,491
Just say something.

219
00:20:03,266 --> 00:20:04,391
So I'll know that I misunderstood.

220
00:20:10,191 --> 00:20:11,341
I'll leave now.

221
00:20:13,716 --> 00:20:15,841
I can't stand looking at you.

222
00:20:18,616 --> 00:20:19,616
Ram, hold on.

223
00:20:23,341 --> 00:20:24,891
Don't tell anyone about it, okay?

224
00:20:32,116 --> 00:20:32,941
Don't worry.

225
00:20:36,816 --> 00:20:38,516
I promise, I won't tell anyone.

226
00:20:43,091 --> 00:20:44,941
Because I don't want them to suffer as I do.

227
00:21:24,716 --> 00:21:28,266
Hubby, your wife is back.

228
00:21:32,591 --> 00:21:34,316
Your wife is back.

229
00:21:36,941 --> 00:21:38,716
Why did you get so drunk for a contest?

230
00:21:39,116 --> 00:21:42,116
The people there were so formidable.
How could I pass?

231
00:21:44,016 --> 00:21:46,191
Let's drink beer to celebrate that I lost.

232
00:21:50,616 --> 00:21:53,316
You're not getting drunk just because you lost.

233
00:21:53,866 --> 00:21:55,066
What happened? Tell me.

234
00:21:59,141 --> 00:22:01,441
Let's go back. Or else your wife will scold.

235
00:22:01,441 --> 00:22:02,516
Whose wife?

236
00:22:02,516 --> 00:22:03,141
Your wife.

237
00:22:03,241 --> 00:22:04,741
Oh? I have a wife?

238
00:22:04,741 --> 00:22:05,666
I borrowed it.

239
00:22:05,666 --> 00:22:06,416
Let's go, brother.

240
00:22:08,441 --> 00:22:11,116
Walk straight.

241
00:22:25,166 --> 00:22:25,766
Cool Boy.

242
00:22:26,966 --> 00:22:28,216
Why are you standing here?

243
00:22:29,991 --> 00:22:31,041
It's going to rain soon.

244
00:22:40,041 --> 00:22:41,541
Tell me. What happened?

245
00:22:41,816 --> 00:22:43,566
I've told you there's nothing.

246
00:22:44,066 --> 00:22:45,841
If you're not telling me, then go back.

247
00:22:46,291 --> 00:22:49,341
Okay. You'll chase me away
no matter what I say.

248
00:22:49,791 --> 00:22:51,416
I have no value anymore, right?

249
00:22:51,816 --> 00:22:53,416
That's why everyone is chasing me away.

250
00:22:53,516 --> 00:22:54,491
Who chased you away?

251
00:22:57,666 --> 00:22:59,041
Fon's manager.

252
00:22:59,616 --> 00:23:01,166
She found out that Fon and I have a relationship.

253
00:23:01,416 --> 00:23:03,191
She told me not to bother Fon.

254
00:23:04,041 --> 00:23:05,091
What did you say then?

255
00:23:10,091 --> 00:23:11,291
Do I have a choice?

256
00:23:12,441 --> 00:23:13,616
What she said is the truth.

257
00:23:15,516 --> 00:23:17,716
Fon has a bright future.

258
00:23:18,091 --> 00:23:21,466
She shouldn't be with useless trash like me.

259
00:23:22,041 --> 00:23:23,716
No one cares about me.

260
00:23:23,716 --> 00:23:24,991
Stop scolding yourself.

261
00:23:27,916 --> 00:23:28,566
What?

262
00:23:30,116 --> 00:23:31,666
Why can't I scold myself?

263
00:23:32,516 --> 00:23:34,941
I'm useless, I'm trash.

264
00:23:34,991 --> 00:23:37,316
I'm low and inferior. No one cares about me.

265
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:44,625
♪I want to tell you, beautiful love has no rules♪

266
00:23:45,125 --> 00:23:51,975
♪No matter male or female, as long as you love me♪

267
00:23:52,550 --> 00:24:00,050
♪Most importantly, someone knows my thought♪

268
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:03,391
♪Leave the rules aside♪

269
00:24:03,391 --> 00:24:04,341
What joke are you making?

270
00:24:04,341 --> 00:24:05,891
♪Let our love grow♪

271
00:24:05,891 --> 00:24:07,296
Even if...

272
00:24:07,297 --> 00:24:08,691
You don't have to do that.

273
00:24:08,691 --> 00:24:09,850
♪Let our love grow♪

274
00:24:14,616 --> 00:24:15,516
What's going on?

275
00:24:17,491 --> 00:24:19,241
Do you think I was joking?

276
00:24:27,141 --> 00:24:29,716
All the while,
